 II. [<span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎עַשְׁתָּרוֺת‎</span>] **noun plural feminine** only construct in phrase <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎עַשְׁתְּר(וֺ)ת צאֶֹ נ֑ךָ‎</span> [[Deut.7.13|Deut 7:13]]; [[Deut.28.4|Deut 28:4]]; [[Deut.28.18|Deut 28:18]]; [[Deut.28.51|Deut 28:51]] (all \|\| <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎שְׁגַר אֲלָפֶיךָ‎</span>) usually interpreted either as 
$\quad$ $\quad$ **a.** = ***ewes*** ([[BDB#Thes|Thes]]) or as 
$\quad$ $\quad$ **b.** = ***young*** (compare ***veneres gregis***; in either case with reference to ***±Aštart*** as goddess of fecundity; [[BDB#RS|RS]]<sup>Semitic i. 292, 457 f., 2nd ed. 310, 476 f.</sup>, adopting **b**, thinks one type of <abbr title="transliteration"><u>±Ašt</u></abbr> in Canaan had form of sheep, so [[BDB#Dr|Dr]]<sup>[[Deut.7.13|Deut 7:13]]</sup>); compare also <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> as name of land fertilized by dew and rain [[BDB#We|We]]<sup>Skizzen iii. 170</sup>.
